<td id="title_text"><h1><a title="Characters Per Inch" class="currentChild" href="Characters_Per_Inch">Characters Per Inch</a></h1></td>



</tr></table>
</td>
</tr></table></div>



<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
A measurement of type, used in <a title="Copyfitting" href="Copyfitting">copyfitting</a>, based on the <a title="Alphabet Length" href="Alphabet_Length">alphabet length</a> of a particular <a title="Typeface" href="Typeface">typeface</a>. When type needs to fit in a certain allotted portion of space, it is often necessary to determine how many characters fit in a unit of linear distance. See <a title="Copyfitting" href="Copyfitting">Copyfitting</a>, <a title="Alphabet Length" href="Alphabet_Length">Alphabet Length</a>, and <a title="Character Count" href="Character_Count">Character Count</a>. See also <a title="Characters Per Pica" href="Characters_Per_Pica">Characters Per Pica</a>. 
</p>
<p id="l3">
'CPI<em> is also used as a measurement of the density of information that can be stored on a magnetic tape, disk, or other type of external storage medium. (See also <a title="Bits Per Inch" href="Bits_Per_Inch">Bits Per Inch</a>.) 
</p>
